olive oil
1 Sourdough Loaf
1 tomato
1 clove garlic
1 packet Single Cream Brie
½ tbs honey
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
2 packet prosciutto
1 packet Pitted Mixed Olives
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet basil pesto

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced.
• Slice the sourdough loaf into 2cm thick slices. Toast or grill to your liking.
• Cut tomato into wedges. Thinly slice garlic.

• Score single cream brie in a crisscross pattern.
• Place brie in a small lined baking dish and press garlic into the slits.
• Drizzle with olive oil and the honey and bake, until softened, 5-7 minutes.
• When done, carefully transfer to serving board.

• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato, a drizzle of
vinegar and olive oil. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.

• Arrange the baked brie, prosciutto, pitted mixed olives, roasted almonds,
toasted sourdough, basil pesto and tomato salad on a serving platter. Enjoy!